  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I suspect it was the same people who got a whiff of his pending arrest.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That one I don't know at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I can only speculate that possibly it also had to do with the fact that he started, which must have been around shortly before he left, maybe 1935, a process at the-- what's called the Reich [INAUDIBLE], the office that had to do with family structure, started a process that was called Arisierung, or Aryanization, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in the hope to escape the anti-Semitic persecution for himself and his family that way.",
      "word_count": 74
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that case was built on the-- on the notion that he wasn't at all the child of my grandparents, but that his real father was a Hungarian general by the name of [?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Erdent von Banitsky, ?] [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] who, so goes the saga, stayed some time in the house of my grandparents in Breslau and conceived and-- and-- and-- and was really Father's father.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, that-- that story [LAUGHS] was corroborated by a funny accident apparently.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this is that the skull measurements, on which [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] these cases were usually determined at that time, lacking the chemistry of today-- skull measurements were identical apparently, this Hungarian general and-- and my father.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And how they ever figured out, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But so I suspect that the arrest probably had to do with the fact that this was such an obvious-- obvious lie.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Probably somebody thought so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That probably had to do with it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But that's pure speculation.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I really don't know that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Fact is that he left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He lived in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He lived in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
